        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): add append streaming content mode",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add `streamingContentMode` for Feishu streaming cards with default `\"full\"` behavior preserved.\n- Add opt-in `\"append\"` mode that sends only newly appended content to the CardKit content endpoint for deployments where repeated full-content updates create severe Feishu-side latency.\n- Document the setting and add regression coverage for append-mode streaming update and close payloads.\n\nFixes #91941.\n\n## Context\n\n#88335 and #88597 established full-content updates as the default behavior to avoid truncation in Feishu CardKit streaming cards. This PR does not revert that default. It adds an explicit escape hatch for Feishu/Lark deployments where the tenant/client correctly appends content updates and full accumulated payloads make long replies slow.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `npx -y pnpm@11.2.2 exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-feishu.config.ts extensions/feishu/src/streaming-card.test.ts`\n- `npx -y pnpm@11.2.2 test:extension feishu`\n- `npx -y pnpm@11.2.2 tsgo:extensions`\n- `git diff --check`\n",
